theHarvester

1. Overview
theHarvester is an OSINT email, domain, and subdomain enumeration tool used in the early reconnaissance phase.

Useful for:
- Bug Bounty recon  
- Gathering emails for password spraying tests  
- Finding virtual hosts and subdomains  

2. Key Features
- Enumeration via search engines (Google, Bing, DuckDuckGo)  
- Passive DNS lookup  
- Subdomain discovery  
- Email harvesting  
- Shodan & Censys integration  

---

3. Installation
### Linux
sudo apt install theharvester


or from GitHub:
git clone https://github.com/laramies/theHarvester
cd theHarvester
pip install -r requirements.txt

macOS
brew install theharvester

Windows
Install via Python:
pip install theHarvester

4. Common Commands
theharvester -d example.com -b google
theharvester -d example.com -b bing -l 500
theharvester -d example.com -b shodan

5. Important Parameters
Flag	Description
-d	Domain
-b	Data source (google, bing, duckduckgo, shodanâ€¦)
-l	Number of results
-f	Output to HTML/XML
-s	Start result number
-v	Verbose mode
-h	Help

6. Advanced Usage
Export to HTML
theharvester -d example.com -b google -f report
API-Powered Scan (Shodan)

export SHODAN_API_KEY="xyz"
theharvester -d example.com -b shodan

